On National Wildland Firefighter Day, the author expresses gratitude for the brave men and women who protect communities and natural resources from wildfires. The article highlights the increasing challenges faced by firefighters due to climate change, hazardous fuels in forests, and changing land development patterns. The author acknowledges the sacrifices made by firefighters who spend months away from their families to save lives and property. The administration is prioritizing support for wildland firefighters, including pay increases, programs for mental and physical health, and creating more job opportunities. Efforts are also being made to reduce the risk of catastrophic fires through increased funding for hazardous fuels management. The article mentions the annual Week of Remembrance, where fallen firefighters are honored, and emphasizes the commitment to firefighter safety. The author concludes by expressing blessings for firefighters and their families across the nation.